            "description": "This was an international project called iTHEPHY, where I have been involved with two other students from the University of Clermont-Auvergne and the Technische Universit\u00e4t of Dortmund. We worked in a data analysis project using data coming from the ATLAS experiment at CERN to look for the heavy vector boson called W' in order to improve the experimental sensitivity and the exclusion limit of its decay using Machine Learning (ML) techniques. Each of us focused on one ML technique (Multilayer Perceptron, Boosted Decision Trees and Support Vector Machine) and we showed that both the\nsignificance and the exclusion limit of the W' were improved.",
